are there other people out there with relatives with alzheimer's disease my mother has this dreaded disease and i was wondering how others are dealing with it any experiences you care to share and how you are dealing with this would be helpful to me and my family my husband's grandmother had alzheimer's disease she had it for almost years my mother in law moved in with her to take care of her it was hard on her but she says that she would do it again when nola first got the disease she tried to leave home and succeeded many times finally they had to put screen wire around the porches with a lock on the doors after the disease progressed some she stopped trying to flee taking care of her then wasn't near as bad then i know alzheimer's isn't a laughing matter but there were times when nola would say or do something and you just had to laugh about it she was even more playful at times for christmas one year we bought her a baby doll she loved taking care of that doll i guess she thought it was real at times her sons were embarrassed by it at first but when they saw how much she enjoyed it they bought a couple for her themselves it's not an easy job taking care of someone with alzheimer's if you can handle taking care of them then that's a wonderful thing if you can't handle the stress that comes with it that's okay too just remember if you have to have help with your mother's care visit her show her you love her that's all that matters Pitaten Alzheimer's disease EastEnders Knots Landing Urinary incontinence Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Care Bears Kodocha Dead Like Me Marilyn Monroe Piccolo Junior Saga Love Hina main characters Neighbours Social rule Fire Emblem: Blazing Sword Too Short a Season (TNG episode) Friends AFI 100 Years series Cliff Richard Jon Secada Only Fools and Horses Abortion debate Avenue Q Springfield Elementary School The Inside The Ashlee Simpson Show The Critic Charmed Everwood Occupational Therapy Juliana of the Netherlands The Amber Spyglass Trai